title: SmartPhos: a pipeline for processing and analysis of phosphoproteomic data
text: Phosphoproteomics provides rich information dissecting pathway activities therefore becoming vital basic translational biomedical research. facilitate streamline phosphoproteomics data analysis, developed SmartPhos, R package pre-processing, quality control, exploratory analysis phosphoproteomics data generated mass-spectrometry. SmartPhos can process outputs MaxQuant Spectronaut either using R command line interactive ShinyApp called SmartPhos Explorer. Besides commonly used preprocessing steps, normalization, transformation, imputation, batch effect correction, package features novel method correcting normalization artifacts observed phosphoproteomics, especially large global phosphorylation changes expected, taking phospho-enriched unenriched samples account. addition, SmartPhos Explorer ShinyApp included R package provides user-friendly interactive one-stop solution performing exploratory data analysis (PCA, hierarchical clustering, etc.), differential expression, time-series clustering, gene set enrichment analysis, kinase activity analysis easily without knowledge coding underlying statistical model. vignette focuses using SmartPhos R command line.

title: SmartPhos: a pipeline for processing and analysis of phosphoproteomic data
text: install SmartPhos enter following R console Load package Load R object
code: if (!requireNamespace("BiocManager", quietly = TRUE))     install.packages("BiocManager") BiocManager::install("SmartPhos") library(MultiAssayExperiment) library(SmartPhos) data("dia_example") dia_example ## A MultiAssayExperiment object of 2 listed ##  experiments with user-defined names and respective classes. ##  Containing an ExperimentList class object of length 2: ##  [1] Phosphoproteome: SummarizedExperiment with 500 rows and 47 columns ##  [2] Proteome: SummarizedExperiment with 500 rows and 47 columns ## Functionality: ##  experiments() - obtain the ExperimentList instance ##  colData() - the primary/phenotype DataFrame ##  sampleMap() - the sample coordination DataFrame ##  `$`, `[`, `[[` - extract colData columns, subset, or experiment ##  *Format() - convert into a long or wide DataFrame ##  assays() - convert ExperimentList to a SimpleList of matrices ##  exportClass() - save data to flat files

text: SmartPhos package performs pre-filtering preprocessing based various threshold values generation multiAssayExperiment object. top , panel different options preprocessing selected assay. options provided shiny app follows: Normalization correction: option present phophoproteomics data present. allows correction normalization artefacts introduced Spectronaut. Normalize phospho intensity corresponding protein expression. Transformation: transformation methods available : log2 vst (variance stabilizing transformation). Normalization: Normalization strategy depends selected transformation method. Therefore, user option Yes . user selects Yes, log2 transformation, median scaling applied vst, vsn applied. Missing values: Users can select percentage missing values allowed. Proteins missing values selected threshold removed analyses. QRILC (Quantile Regression Imputation Left-Censored data) MinDet (Deterministic minimal value approach) BPCA (Bayesian PCA) MLE (Maximum Likelihood Estimation) Random forest Batch effects removal: option provides abilty correct batch effects. uses removeBatchEffect() limma package. users can select maximum two columns. columns used batch effects removal present fileTable.txt file. preprocessing (transformation, normalization, imputation, etc.) intensity assay can performed running following command:

title: SmartPhos: a pipeline for processing and analysis of phosphoproteomic data
text: goal performing differential expression analysis quantify expression levels genes different experimental conditions using statistical tests. users want paired t-test patient IDs, cell lines, etc, users must subjectID one column fileTable.txt file relevant information. subjectID column also selected additional column annotations generation multiAssayExperiment object. performDifferentialExp() two methods performing differential expression analysis: limma: uses linear models. ProDA: uses probabilistic dropout model. Limma method needs assay non-missing data faster proDA method. ProDA method can work assay missing values also. ‘dea’ list object contains two values: ‘resDE’ tabular differential expression analysis results ‘seSub’ subsetted SummarizedExperiment object based selected condition. Plot volcano plot obtained differential expression analysis results running following command:  pFilter fcFilter arguments can used change thresholds upregulated downregulated genes represented volcano plot. title: SmartPhos: a pipeline for processing and analysis of phosphoproteomic data
text: Time series clustering performed group proteins/phosphopeptides based level changes time. clusterTS() function employs fuzzy c-means clustering algorithm considers time-resolved trend, expression levels. Thus, members cluster similar trend time (e.g., increasing decreasing), though expression level can different. use function, users must logitudinal data timepoint annotation data. time points either unit-less numbers (e.g., 1, 2, 3) hour /minute, must typed “h” “min”, respectively (e.g., 1min, 2min, 3h). Please notice mixing two said options (e.g., 1, 2min, 3) using unit time (e.g., 1hour, 2minute, 3day) likely lead wrong results. ‘tsc’ list object contains two values: ‘cluster’ tabular time series clustering results ‘plot’ clusters plots.  single gene phospho-site time series data can also plotted:
code: # call addZeroTime function to add zero timepoint to EGF treatment newSEzero <- addZeroTime(newSE, condition = "treatment", treat = "EGF",                           zeroTreat = "1stCrtl",                           timeRange = c("10min","100min", "24h")) # extract the assay exprMat <- SummarizedExperiment::assay(newSEzero) # call the clustering function tsc <- clusterTS(x = exprMat, k = 5) tsc$cluster ## # A tibble: 580 × 7 ##    feature time                    value cluster   prob  cNum clusterNum    ##    <fct>   <fct>                   <dbl> <chr>    <dbl> <int> <chr>         ##  1 s499    Phospho_EGF_10min_rep2  14.1  cluster1 0.402    10 cluster1 (10) ##  2 s499    Phospho_EGF_10min_rep3  14.1  cluster1 0.402    10 cluster1 (10) ##  3 s499    Phospho_EGF_100min_rep2 14.3  cluster1 0.402    10 cluster1 (10) ##  4 s499    Phospho_EGF_100min_rep3 12.5  cluster1 0.402    10 cluster1 (10) ##  5 s499    Phospho_EGF_10min_rep1   8.96 cluster1 0.402    10 cluster1 (10) ##  6 s499    Phospho_EGF_24h_rep1    14.5  cluster1 0.402    10 cluster1 (10) ##  7 s499    Phospho_EGF_100min_rep1 14.6  cluster1 0.402    10 cluster1 (10) ##  8 s499    Phospho_EGF_0min_rep2   14.2  cluster1 0.402    10 cluster1 (10) ##  9 s499    Phospho_EGF_0min_rep3   14.2  cluster1 0.402    10 cluster1 (10) ## 10 s499    Phospho_EGF_0min_rep1   13.6  cluster1 0.402    10 cluster1 (10) ## # ℹ 570 more rows tsc$plot timerange <- unique(newSEzero$timepoint) plotTimeSeries(newSEzero, type = "expression", geneID = "s40",                 symbol = "RBM47_T519", condition = "treatment",                 treatment = "EGF", timerange = timerange)

title: SmartPhos: a pipeline for processing and analysis of phosphoproteomic data
text: Enrichment analysis can performed either gene sets (gene-centric) post-translational modification signature sets (site-centric) differentially expressed time-series cluster. latter, set contains PTM site names direction regulation (- -regulated) instead gene names. phosphorylation sites considered since pipeline supports proteomics phosphoproteomics data. gene sets PTM signature sets derived Molecular Signatures Database (Subramanian, Tamayo et al.,2005; Liberzon et al., 2011, Liberzon et al., 2015) PTM Signature Database version 2.0.0 (Krug et al., 2019), respectively. Users encouraged consult PTMsigDB website (https://proteomics.broadapps.org/ptmsigdb/) paper Krug et al. details PTM signature sets curated annotation. gene-centric pathway enrichment, users can perform either Parametric Analysis Gene Set Enrichment (PAGE) (Kim & Volsky, 2005) Gene Set Enrichment Analysis (GSEA) (Subramanian, Tamayo et al.,2005) Differential Expression analysis result. Time series clustering result, offer Fisher’s exact test. phospho-signature enrichment Differential Expression analysis result, offer PTM-Signature Enrichment Analysis (PTM-SEA), method adapted GSEA Krug et al. (2019) applicable PTM Signature Database. time series clustering result, offer Fisher’s exact test, signature set split two, one containing upregulated downregulated phosphosites.

title: SmartPhos: a pipeline for processing and analysis of phosphoproteomic data
text: SmartPhos can perform kinase activity inference based phosphopeptides differentially expressed cluster. Similar enrichment analysis, users first need perform either differential expression analysis time-series clustering select cluster interest. network kinase-phosphosite interactions constructed using package OmnipathR (Türei et al., 2021). Users can choose construct network prior knowledge either Homo sapiens (taxonomy ID = 9606) Mus musculus (taxonomy ID = 10090). combining prior knowledge known kinase-phosphosite interactions data, SmartPhos can infer activity kinases responsible phosphopeptides considered. activity estimated activity score computed package decoupleR (Badia--Mompel et al., 2022) following authors’ tutorial Kinase Transcription Factor activity estimation. time-series clustering, users can also estimate likely kinases associated phosphopeptides selected cluster.

what: Kinase activity inference on differential expression analysis results
title: SmartPhos: a pipeline for processing and analysis of phosphoproteomic data
code: netw <- getDecouplerNetwork("Homo sapiens") scoreTab <- calcKinaseScore(dea$resDE, netw, statType = "stat", nPerm = 500)

Users can make independent directory SmartPhos Explorer app open script (server.R, ui.R) RStudio click Run App button. front page Shiny app looks :  current tabs : Preprocessing PCA Heatmap Differential expression Time-series clustering Enrichment analysis Kinase activity inference Log Info Update Notes vignette, walk process preparing data performing downstream analyses using different tabs Shiny app.

title: SmartPhos Explorer: a one-stop data analysis platform for proteomic and phosphoproteomic data
text: file tab-separated tsv file contains information including name quantification table, sample ID experimental details, whether certain sample enriched phospho-peptides, whether quantification protein groups phosphorylation sites . Optional annotations, experimental conditions, time points etc. can also included table required specific downstream analysis tasks. error message displayed file missing format file incorrect. mandatory columns table follows: fileName: names quantification tables protein groups phosphorylation sites. standard output files Spectronaut MaxQuant. Make sure contains file names file extension (example: “20240826_Protein_Report.xls”, “20240826_PTMReport.xls”)) relative absolute path. Important notes format quantification table Spectronaut: quantification table Spectronaut “wide” format, different samples different columns. table plain text format, Excel tables. file extension matter. Spectronaut sometimes output .xls files actually plain text files. acceptable deliminators tables : tab ( (preferred), comma (,), colon (:) semicolon (;). full proteome measurement, “PG.ProteinGroups”, “PG.Genes” “[sample name]PG.Quantity” columns must present. phosphoproteome measurement, “[sample name]PTM.SiteProbability”, “[sample name]PTM.Quantity”, “PTM.CollapseKey”, “PG.UniProtIds”,“PG.Genes”, “PTM.SiteLocation”, “PTM.SiteAA”, “PTM.FlankingRegion” columns must present. id: Contains unique identifiers sample (sample IDs). sample IDs correspond prefix actual column names quantification table. example: ID value FullProteome_1stCrtl_0min_rep2 corresponds one column names oecf4_220602_BH_ET_FullProteome_1stCrtl_0min_rep2.raw.PG.Quantity quantification table. SmartPhos automatically recognize columns quantification table match certain sample ID, long sample ID present columns contain “PG.Quantity”. searchType: Contains information type search performed samples Spectronaut MaxQuant. two possibilities: proteome (quantification protein abundance) phosphoproteome (quantification abundance phosphorylation sites). two searchTypes represented two assays multiAssayExperiment object. Note app still work one searchType present functions may available. example, normalisation phosphorylation sites protein abundance available phosphoproteome measurement available. sampleType: Contains information whether enrichment phosphorylated peptides performed certain sample. sampleType can Phospho (PP) phospho-enriched samples FullProteome (FP) non-enriched sample. app still work one sample type present functions may available. example, novel normalisation correction phosphoproteomic data available full proteome without enrichment absent. mentioned columns mandatory ones. , fileTable.txt can contain optional columns : sampleName column important performing normalization correction normalizing Phosphoproteome samples Full Proteome samples. sample id without FP_/PP_ Phospho_/FullProteome_ suffix prefix. example, sample ID, FullProteome_1stCrtl_0min_rep1, sampleName , “1stCrtl_0min_rep1”. code: library(SummarizedExperiment) # Load multiAssayExperiment object data("dia_example") # Get SummarizedExperiment object se <- dia_example[["Phosphoproteome"]] colData(se) <- colData(dia_example) seProcess <- preprocessPhos(seData = se, normalize = TRUE, impute = "QRILC") #> Imputing along margin 2 (samples/columns). result <- addZeroTime(seProcess, condition = "treatment", treat = "EGF", zeroTreat = "1stCrtl", timeRange = c("20min","40min", "6h")) # Get the numeric matrix exprMat <- SummarizedExperiment::assay(result) # Call the clustering function clust <- clusterTS(x = exprMat, k = 3) genesetPath <- appDir <- system.file("shiny-app/geneset", package = "SmartPhos") inGMT <- piano::loadGSC(paste0(genesetPath, "/Cancer_Hallmark.gmt"),type="gmt") # Call the function clusterEnrich(clust$cluster, seProcess, inGMT) #> $table #> # A tibble: 0 × 9 #> # ℹ 9 variables: Name <chr>, Gene.number <int>, Set.size <int>, pval <dbl>, #> #   Genes <list>, padj <dbl>, cluster <chr>, ifSig <lgl>, atLeast1 <lgl> #>  #> $plot  #>

title: Perform Enrichment analysis on differentially expressed genes or phospho-sites — enrichDifferential
text: enrichDifferential performs enrichment analysis differentially expressed genes phospho-sites either pathway phospho-specific enrichment, depending input parameters. supports multiple statistical methods PAGE GSEA pathway enrichment Kolmogorov-Smirnov approach phospho-enrichment.

title: Perform Enrichment analysis on differentially expressed genes or phospho-sites — enrichDifferential
code: enrichDifferential(   dea,   type = c("Pathway enrichment", "Phospho-signature enrichment"),   gsaMethod = c("PAGE", "GSEA"),   geneSet,   ptmSet,   statType = c("stat", "log2FC"),   nPerm = 100,   sigLevel = 0.05,   ifFDR = FALSE )

title: Perform Enrichment analysis on differentially expressed genes or phospho-sites — enrichDifferential
text: dea data frame containing differential expression analysis results. include columns like   `pvalue`, `Gene` (`site`), `stat`, `log2FC`. type character string indicating type enrichment. Options `"Pathway enrichment"` `"Phospho-signature enrichment"`. gsaMethod character string specifying gene set analysis method pathway enrichment. Options `"PAGE"` `"GSEA"`. geneSet gene set collection use pathway enrichment. ptmSet post-translational modification (PTM) set database phospho-enrichment analysis. statType character string specifying statistic type use. Options `"stat"` `"log2FC"`. nPerm numeric specifying number permutations GSEA. Default 100. sigLevel numeric value representing significance threshold filtering results. Ddefault 0.05. ifFDR logical value indicating whether filter results using FDR-adjusted p-values. Default `FALSE`.

title: Perform Enrichment analysis on differentially expressed genes or phospho-sites — enrichDifferential
text: data frame containing results enrichment analysis, including columns gene set name,   statistical significance, adjusted p-values.

title: Perform Enrichment analysis on differentially expressed genes or phospho-sites — enrichDifferential
text: `enrichDifferential` function performs either pathway enrichment phospho-enrichment analysis based `type` parameter. pathway enrichment, uses either PAGE GSEA method provided gene set collection. phospho-enrichment, uses Kolmogorov-Smirnov test PTM set database. Results can filtered significance level optionally adjusted FDR.

title: Perform Enrichment analysis on differentially expressed genes or phospho-sites — enrichDifferential
code: library(SummarizedExperiment) library(piano) # Load multiAssayExperiment object data("dia_example") # Get SummarizedExperiment object se <- dia_example[["Phosphoproteome"]] colData(se) <- colData(dia_example) # Preprocess the proteome assay result <- preprocessPhos(se, normalize = TRUE) # Call the function to perform differential expression analyis dea <- performDifferentialExp(se = result, assay = "Intensity", method = "limma", reference = "1stCrtl", target = "EGF", condition = "treatment") # Load the gene set genesetPath <- appDir <- system.file("shiny-app/geneset", package = "SmartPhos") inGMT <- loadGSC(paste0(genesetPath,"/Cancer_Hallmark.gmt"),type="gmt") # Call the function resTab <- enrichDifferential(dea = dea$resDE, type = "Pathway enrichment", gsaMethod = "PAGE", geneSet = inGMT, statType = "stat", nPerm = 200, sigLevel = 0.05, ifFDR = FALSE) #> Running gene set analysis: #> Checking arguments...done! #> Final gene/gene-set association: 20 genes and 22 gene sets #>   Details: #>   Calculating gene set statistics from 20 out of 65 gene-level statistics #>   Removed 4366 genes from GSC due to lack of matching gene statistics #>   Removed 28 gene sets containing no genes after gene removal #>   Removed additionally 0 gene sets not matching the size limits #>   Loaded additional information for 22 gene sets #> Calculating gene set statistics...done! #> Calculating gene set significance...done! #> Adjusting for multiple testing...done!

text: se SummarizedExperiment object containing data. id Character. identifier gene feature plot. symbol Character. symbol name gene feature use plot title.

title: Plot Boxplot of Intensity Data — intensityBoxPlot
text: ggplot2 object representing boxplot intensity data.

title: Plot Boxplot of Intensity Data — intensityBoxPlot
text: function generates boxplot intensity data specified gene feature SummarizedExperiment (SE) object. plot shows distribution normalized intensities across different groups specified comparison column SE object. function can handle grouped data repeated measures: - SE object contain subjectID column, function plots standard boxplot grouped comparison column. - SE object contains subjectID column, function adds lines connecting points subject across groups, providing visual indication subject-specific changes. boxplot customized various aesthetic elements, box width, transparency, point size, axis labels, title formatting.

title: Plot Boxplot of Intensity Data — intensityBoxPlot
code: library(SummarizedExperiment) # Load multiAssayExperiment object data("dda_example") # Get SummarizedExperiment object se <- dda_example[["Proteome"]] colData(se) <- colData(dda_example) # Preprocess the proteome assay result <- preprocessProteome(se, normalize = TRUE) # Call the function to perform differential expression analyis de <- performDifferentialExp(se = result, assay = "Intensity", method = "limma", reference = "1stCrtl", target = "EGF", condition = "treatment") # Plot the box plot for the given id and symbol intensityBoxPlot(de$seSub, "p99", "PPP6C")

title: Scale and Center a Matrix — mscale
text: x numeric matrix rows features columns samples. center Logical. TRUE, rows centered subtracting mean median. Default TRUE. scale Logical. TRUE, rows scaled dividing standard deviation mean absolute deviation. Default TRUE. censor numeric vector length one two censoring scaled values. length one, values censored symmetrically positive negative values. length two, first value lower limit second value upper limit. Default NULL. useMad Logical. TRUE, mean absolute deviation used scaling instead standard deviation. Default FALSE.

title: Scale and Center a Matrix — mscale
text: scaled centered numeric matrix dimensions input matrix `x`.

title: Scale and Center a Matrix — mscale
text: function allows flexible scaling centering rows matrix: center scale TRUE, rows   centered scaled. center TRUE, rows centered   scaled. scale TRUE, rows scaled   centered. neither center scale TRUE,   original matrix returned. function can also censor extreme values, either symmetrically asymmetrically, based censor parameter.

title: Scale and Center a Matrix — mscale
code: # Create a sample matrix (3 rows by 5 columns) sample_matrix <- matrix(c(1:15), nrow = 3, byrow = TRUE)  # Scale and center the matrix using the default settings mscale(sample_matrix, center = TRUE, scale = TRUE) #>           [,1]       [,2] [,3]      [,4]     [,5] #> [1,] -1.264911 -0.6324555    0 0.6324555 1.264911 #> [2,] -1.264911 -0.6324555    0 0.6324555 1.264911 #> [3,] -1.264911 -0.6324555    0 0.6324555 1.264911  # Only center the matrix without scaling mscale(sample_matrix, center = TRUE, scale = FALSE) #>      [,1] [,2] [,3] [,4] [,5] #> [1,]   -2   -1    0    1    2 #> [2,]   -2   -1    0    1    2 #> [3,]   -2   -1    0    1    2  # Only scale the matrix without centering mscale(sample_matrix, center = FALSE, scale = TRUE) #>           [,1]     [,2]     [,3]     [,4]     [,5] #> [1,] 0.6324555 1.264911 1.897367 2.529822 3.162278 #> [2,] 3.7947332 4.427189 5.059644 5.692100 6.324555 #> [3,] 6.9570109 7.589466 8.221922 8.854377 9.486833

title: Normalize Phosphoproteome by Full Proteome — normByFullProteome
code: # load mae object data("dia_example") # call the function normByFullProteome(dia_example) #> harmonizing input: #>   removing 27 sampleMap rows with 'colname' not in colnames of experiments #> A MultiAssayExperiment object of 2 listed #>  experiments with user-defined names and respective classes. #>  Containing an ExperimentList class object of length 2: #>  [1] Phosphoproteome: SummarizedExperiment with 4 rows and 20 columns #>  [2] Proteome: SummarizedExperiment with 500 rows and 47 columns #> Functionality: #>  experiments() - obtain the ExperimentList instance #>  colData() - the primary/phenotype DataFrame #>  sampleMap() - the sample coordination DataFrame #>  `$`, `[`, `[[` - extract colData columns, subset, or experiment #>  *Format() - convert into a long or wide DataFrame #>  assays() - convert ExperimentList to a SimpleList of matrices #>  exportClass() - save data to flat files

title: Perform Differential Expression Analysis — performDifferentialExp
text: function designed facilitate differential expression analysis SummarizedExperiment (SE) object. function allows users specify various parameters tailor analysis specific experimental setup. main steps function follows: 1. Sample Selection: Based provided condition, reference, target arguments, function identifies relevant samples analysis. time points (refTime targetTime) provided, refines sample selection. 2. Subsetting SE Object: SE object subsetted include selected samples. new column comparison added colData, indicating whether sample belongs reference target group. 3. Design Matrix Construction: function constructs design matrix differential expression analysis. SE object contains subjectID column, included design account repeated measures paired samples. 4. Differential Expression Analysis: Depending specified method, function performs differential expression analysis using either limma ProDA package:     - Limma: function fits linear model expression data     applies empirical Bayes moderation standard errors.     results extracted formatted.     - ProDA: function fits probabilistic dropout model     expression data tests differential expression. results     extracted formatted. 5. Result Formatting: differential expression results merged metadata SE object, resulting table formatted tibble. table includes columns log2 fold change (log2FC), test statistic (stat), p-value (pvalue), adjusted p-value (padj), gene/feature ID (ID). function returns list containing formatted differential expression results subsetted SE object. allows users explore visualize results needed.
